# Serendib Hospital — Three Ways, One Judge
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is gitignored; this file is not — never put a
# real key here.
#
#     cp .env.example .env
#
# Loaded via python-dotenv. Not every key is required: see "Required for what" below.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# INTEGRITY RULE #3 — the judge must be a DIFFERENT model family than the
# answerers. This project's assignment:
#
#     ANSWERERS  →  OpenAI GPT · Google Gemini · Llama/Qwen (Ollama, Groq)
#     JUDGE      →  Anthropic Claude          ← keep Claude OUT of Phase B
#
# If you ever answer with Claude, the judge is no longer independent and the
# whole comparison is invalid.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── THE JUDGE (Phase C) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Claude scores all ~800 answers against the source documents. Also the
# documented Q&A-generation path in Phase A (`build_dataset generate`).
# REQUIRED for: Phase C.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ── FRONTIER ANSWERERS (Phase B · Step 1 prompting) ──────────────────────────
# OpenAI: frontier prompting baseline.
# ⚠️ NO LONGER the fine-tuning path. OpenAI withdrew self-serve fine-tuning: orgs
# that had not already run a job before 2026-05-07 get `403 training_not_available`,
# on every model. This project is on the wrong side of that date. See docs/cost-analysis.md.
# REQUIRED for: Phase B step 1 (+ step 3 RAG).
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Google Gemini: the second frontier prompting model.
# NB: also cannot fine-tune — the Gemini API/AI Studio dropped tuning entirely
# (it survives only on Vertex AI, behind GCP service-account auth).
# REQUIRED for: Phase B step 1 (optional — drop it and run one frontier model).
GOOGLE_API_KEY=

# ── MANAGED FINE-TUNING (Phase B · Step 2b) ──────────────────────────────────
# Together AI: the surviving managed fine-tuning path. It works precisely because
# it tunes OPEN-WEIGHT models (Qwen/Llama/Mistral) rather than closed frontier ones
# — the same reason the local QLoRA ladder works. LoRA SFT, ~$0.48/1M train tokens.
# Inference is OpenAI-wire compatible, so it rides the existing adapter via base_url.
#   key: https://api.together.ai/settings/api-keys   (billing must be enabled)
# REQUIRED for: Phase B step 2b (optional — the local ladder alone satisfies Step 2).
TOGETHER_API_KEY=

# ── OPEN / SMALL ANSWERERS (Phase B · Step 1) ────────────────────────────────
# Groq: fast hosted Llama/Qwen inference. Optional — the local Ollama models
# below already cover the "small open model" requirement for free.
GROQ_API_KEY=

# OpenRouter: one gateway to many models (uses the OpenAI SDK with a custom
# base_url). Optional fallback if a provider above is unavailable.
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# Alibaba DashScope — hosted Qwen. Optional; the local qwen3.5:9b covers Qwen.
QWEN_API_KEY=

# Hugging Face: base-model downloads for BOTH fine-tuning backends — the local QLoRA
# ladder and the Together-trained adapter (which is downloaded, then served from here).
# REQUIRED for: Phase B step 2 (`uv sync --extra finetune-local`).
#
# NB on Llama: meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct is GATED — it returns 403
# GatedRepoError until Meta grants your account the licence. `ft-llama3.1-8b` therefore
# points at NousResearch/Meta-Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct, an ungated mirror of the identical
# weights (verified: llama, 32 layers, 4096 hidden, 128256 vocab). If you get the licence
# granted, you can switch models.py back to the official repo — the adapter fits either.
HF_TOKEN=

# ── OPTIONAL VECTOR STORE (Phase B · Step 3 RAG) ─────────────────────────────
# The default RAG path is local FAISS + Ollama embeddings — no key, no network.
# Only fill these in if you deliberately move the index to Supabase/pgvector.
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_KEY=

# ── LOCAL MODELS (no key needed) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Ollama serves the open answerers and the RAG embeddings. Just `ollama serve`.
# Models this project expects (see README "Local models"):
#   answerers  : llama3.1:8b · qwen3.5:9b
#   embeddings : nomic-embed-text
OLLAMA_HOST=http://localhost:11434
